 "><span class="YNujN JGtjI aZFDu rkKLh  gtOSm FbbUW tUtYa vOCwz EQwFq yCufu eEak Qmvg nyTIa SRXVc vzLa jgBfc WXDas CiUCW kqbG zrdEG txGfn ygKVe BbezD UOtxr CVfpq xijV soGRS XgdC sEIlf daWqJ ">Photograph courtesy Kleinjan Groenewald, Habitas Atacama</span></div></div></div></div></div></figcaption></figure></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="FITT_Article_main_group_wrapper VZTD UeCOM jIRH oimqG UwdmX Xmrlz ReShI KaJdY lqtkC ssImf HfYhe RTHNs iJVrZ " data-testid="prism-GridContainer"><div class="Kiog kNVGM nvpSA qwdi bmjsw " data-testid="prism-GridRow"><div class="theme-e oBTii mrzah " data-testid="prism-GridColumn" style="--grid-column-span-xxs:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-xs:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-sm:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-md:20;--grid-column-span-lg:16;--grid-column-span-xl:16;--grid-column-span-xxl:14;--grid-column-start-xxs:auto;--grid-column-start-xs:auto;--grid-column-start-sm:auto;--grid-column-start-md:3;--grid-column-start-lg:5;--grid-column-start-xl:5;--grid-column-start-xxl:6"><p class="EkqkG nlgHS yuUao lqtkC TjIXL aGjvy">At the edge of the world’s driest non-polar desert, this <a class="zZygg UbGlr iFzkS qdXbA WCDhQ DbOXS tqUtK GpWVU iJYzE " data-testid="prism-linkbase" href="https://www.ourhabitas.com/atacama/" target="_blank">ecolodge</a> offers nighttime stargazing, morning yoga, and easy access to hiking, biking, and sandboarding in <a class="zZygg UbGlr iFzkS qdXbA WCDhQ DbOXS tqUtK GpWVU iJYzE " data-testid="prism-linkbase" href="https://www.nationalgeographic.com/travel/destination/chile" target="_blank">Chile</a>’s otherworldly landscapes. Cabins—built with native boulders and kitted out with locally crafted rattan accessories and <i>aguayos<!-- --> </i>(Andean woven blankets)— surround a restaurant serving specialties such as dulce de leche pancakes and whitefish ceviche. “There’s something leveling about being surrounded by such natural beauty, whether it’s paragliding above dunes during the day or being engulfed in the stars at night,” says Our Habitas founder Oliver Ripley.</p></div></div></div><div class="NYwzQ vUYNV glxIO ilAoG HPkGR "><div class="natgeo-ad" data-testid="prism-ad-wrapper" style="min-width:728px;min-height:90px;transition:min-height 0.3s linear 0s" data-ad-placeholder="true"><div data-box-type="fitt-adbox-fitt-article-inline-outstream" data-testid="prism-ad"><div class="Ad fitt-article-inline-outstream  ad-slot  " data-slot-type="fitt-article-inline-outstream" data-slot-kvps="pos=fitt-article-inline-outstream-3"></div></div></div></div><div class="FITT_Article_main_group_wrapper VZTD UeCOM jIRH oimqG UwdmX Xmrlz ReShI KaJdY lqtkC ssImf HfYhe RTHNs iJVrZ " data-testid="prism-GridContainer"><div class="Kiog kNVGM nvpSA qwdi bmjsw " data-testid="prism-GridRow"><div class="theme-e oBTii mrzah " data-testid="prism-GridColumn" style="--grid-column-span-xxs:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-xs:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-sm:var(--grid-columns);--grid-column-span-md:20;--grid-column-span-lg:16;--grid-column-span-xl:16;--grid-column-span-xxl:14;--grid-column-start-xxs:auto;--grid-column-start-xs:auto;--grid-column-start-sm:auto;--grid-column-start-md:3;--grid-column-start-lg:5;--grid-column-start-xl:5;--grid-column-start-xxl:6"><p class="EkqkG nlgHS yuUao lqtkC TjIXL aGjvy"><b class="cXscX">Hotelito by MUSA, Zihuatanejo, Mexico</b></p><p class="EkqkG nlgHS yuUao lqtkC TjIXL aGjvy">Private mezcal tastings, surfing lessons, and foraging tours (for everything from chicken and duck eggs to edible flowers, chiles, and fruit) are just some of the experiences available to guests at <a class="zZygg UbGlr iFzkS qdXbA WCDhQ DbOXS tqUtK GpWVU iJYzE " data-testid="prism-linkbase" href="https://stayatmusa.mx/hotelito/" target="_blank">this 13-room resort</a> on <a class="zZygg UbGlr iFzkS qdXbA WCDhQ DbOXS tqUtK GpWVU iJYzE " data-testid="prism-linkbase" href="https://www.nationalgeographic.com/travel/destination/mexico" target="_blank">Mexico</a>’s Pacific shore. A rooftop garden both cools the interior and supplies the onsite restaurant, Alba. At a neighboring turtle sanctuary, guests can volunteer to help hatchlings reach the water.</p><p class="EkqkG nlgHS yuUao lqtkC TjIXL aGjvy"><b class="cXscX">Kimpton Grand Roatán Resort <!-- -->&amp;<!-- --> Spa, Roatán, Honduras</b></p></div></div></div><div class="NYwzQ vUYNV glxIO ilAoG HPkGR "><div><div class="InlineImage GpQCA lZur asrEW " data-testid="prism-inline-image"><figure class="kzIjN GNmeK pYrtp dSqFO " data-testid="prism-figure"><div class="GpQCA lZur Rnci " data-testid="prism-ratio-frame"><div class="FvQLF iLTd NqeUA UzzHi iWsMV "><div class="lZur " data-testid="prism-copyright-wrapper"><picture data-testid="prism-picture"><source media="(max-width: 374px)" srcSet="https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=374&amp;h=210, https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=748&amp;h=420 2x"/><source media="(min-width: 375px) and (max-width: 413px)" srcSet="https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=413&amp;h=232, https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=826&amp;h=464 2x"/><source media="(min-width: 414px) and (max-width: 767px)" srcSet="https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=767&amp;h=431, https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=1534&amp;h=862 2x"/><source media="(min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1024px)" srcSet="https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_Spa1_16x9.jpg?w=1024&amp;h=576, https://i.natgeofe.com/n/2890c861-6385-4ad4-a5fe-3c922194d8e8/Aerial2_Kimpton_GrandRoatanResort_